Class CorrectPackagingRule

    • se.jguru.nazgul.tools.codestyle.enforcer.rules.AbstractEnforcerRule

        • se.jguru.nazgul.tools.codestyle.enforcer.rules.CorrectPackagingRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.maven.enforcer.rule.api.EnforcerRule

    public class CorrectPackagingRule
extends AbstractNonCacheableEnforcerRule
    Enforcer rule to enforce correct packaging for all source files within a project, implying that all source files should be located within or under a package identical to the groupId of the project itself.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB

      • setPackageExtractors

        public final void setPackageExtractors(String packageExtractorImplementations)
                                throws IllegalArgumentException
        Splices the supplied packageExtractorImplementations argument, which is assumed to be a comma-separated string holding fully qualified class names of the PackageExtractor implementations which should be used by this CorrectPackagingRule.
        Parameters:
        packageExtractorImplementations - a comma-separated string holding fully qualified class names of the PackageExtractor implementations. Each such class must have a default (i.e. no-argument) constructor.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the supplied packageExtractorImplementations argument could not yield an instantiated PackageExtractor instance.
